al capitals of China]]\n* [[Mezitli Producer Women's Market#Guangzhou Innovation Award]]\n\n== Notes ==\n{{NoteFoot|40em}}\n\n== References ==\n=== Citations ===\n{{Reflist}}\n\n=== Sources ===\n{{refbegin}}\n* {{citation |url = https://books.google.com/books?id=n8FRAQAAIAAJ |title=An Anglochinese Calendar for the Year 1845, Corresponding to the Year of the Chinese Cycle \u00c6ra 4482 or the 42d Year of the 75th Cycle of Sixty, being the 25th Year of the Reign of Ta'ukwa'ng, ''Vol. II'' |publisher=Office of the Chinese Repository |location=Hong Kong |ref={{harvid|''ACC''|1845}}|year=1845 }}.\n* {{cite EB9 |mode=cs2 |author-link=Robert Kennaway Douglas |first=Robert Kennaway |last=Douglass  |wstitle=Canton (1.) |volume=5  |ref={{harvid|''EB''|1878}} |pages=37\u20139}}\n* {{cite EB1911 |mode=cs2 |author-link=Robert Kennaway Douglas |first=Robert Kennaway |last=Douglass  |wstitle=Canton (China) |volume=5 |ref={{harvid|''EB''|1911}} |pages=218\u2013220 }}\n* {{citation |contribution-url = http://www.britannica.com/EBchecked/topic/93196/Guangzhou |contribution=Guangzhou |title=Encyclop\u00e6dia Britannica'', online ed.'' |last=Kuo |first=Ping-chia |url = http://www.britannica.com |access-date=15 July 2016 |ref={{harvid|''EB''|2016}} |publisher=Encyclop\u00e6dia Britannica}}.\n* {{citation |editor1-first= Trudy |editor1-last=Ring |editor2-first=Robert M. |editor2-last=Salkin |editor3-first=Sharon |editor3-last=La Boda |title=International Dictionary of Historic Places, ''Vol. V:'' Asia and Oceania |year=1996 |publisher=Taylor & Francis |url = https://books.google.com/books?id=vWLRxJEU49EC&printsec=frontcover |isbn=978-1-884964-04-6 |ref={{harvid|''IDHP''|1996}} }}.\n* {{citation |contribution=Guangzhou |pp=[https://books.google.com/books?id=mU31AgAAQBAJ&pg=PA284 284\u2013300] |url = https://books.google.com/books?id=mU31AgAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover |title=Time Out: Hong Kong |publisher=Time Out Guides |location=London |year=2011 |isbn=978-1-84670-114-6 |ref={{harvid|''Tim